column5: WINTER POEM  It's winter in Canada And the gentle breezes blow Seventy Kilometers an hour ...At thirty-five below.  Oh, how I love Canada When the snow's up to your butt You take a breath of winter Your eyes and nose get frozen shut.  Yes, the weather here is wonderful So I guess I'll hang around. I could never leave Canada 'Cause my boots are frozen to the ground!  *sent to me via E-Mail  Randy
No Nick.. that would be 117 KPH
I knew someone was going to say that.
